quads and feet.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.12875,0.20744,0.15901,0.099407,0.072742,0.077177,0.055855,0.062092,0.044545,0.036782,0.030628,0.025578],"unified_progress":[0.12018,0.14897,0.11658,0.10983,0.087774,0.088986,0.070097,0.075584,0.059907,0.049375,0.041186,0.031538]},{"section":5,"text":"Absent ankle and knee reflexes, but sensation is normal.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.099127,0.16698,0.14108,0.10475,0.08518,0.084621,0.069777,0.070323,0.058329,0.04706,0.040204,0.032562],"unified_progress":[0.094092,0.12513,0.11082,0.1076,0.096827,0.093475,0.080597,0.080601,0.071058,0.057042,0.047027,0.035732]},{"section":6,"text":"CSF shows high protein, normal glucose, and a bit elevated cells.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.072292,0.12621,0.12916,0.11641,0.10058,0.08971,0.082948,0.074535,0.065447,0.056107,0.049198,0.037404],"unified_progress":[0.063252,0.10774,0.11064,0.10929,0.11109,0.099155,0.09497,0.081369,0.072581,0.061516,0.051686,0.036711]},{"section":7,"text":"Hmm, first, the symptoms started after a respiratory illness.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.065971,0.1111,0.12103,0.11626,0.1029,0.088148,0.080922,0.073878,0.065723,0.06782,0.05461,0.051643],"unified_progress":[0.07111,0.087342,0.093148,0.1061,0.099121,0.0932,0.090714,0.086771,0.079433,0.079293,0.064568,0.049198]},{"section":8,"text":"That makes me think of a post-infectious autoimmune process.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050697,0.097649,0.11628,0.11695,0.10616,0.092424,0.085389,0.077401,0.070215,0.073068,0.058555,0.055216],"unified_progress":[0.051829,0.080468,0.090804,0.10042,0.098749,0.096154,0.094733,0.090302,0.084805,0.085535,0.070165,0.056033]},{"section":9,"text":"The weakness is ascending?","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046279,0.092737,0.10556,0.10691,0.1015,0.093842,0.090504,0.084995,0.078515,0.076609,0.066206,0.056348],"unified_progress":[0.083355,0.081134,0.086326,0.093004,0.093594,0.091334,0.091238,0.089889,0.083522,0.083248,0.06902,0.054336]},{"section":10,"text":"Wait, she started with tingling in the feet and now leg weakness.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.081537,0.13357,0.11,0.093125,0.08617,0.087979,0.081018,0.08187,0.071714,0.065519,0.057884,0.049618],"unified_progress":[0.092335,0.11883,0.10218,0.09199,0.087644,0.088494,0.081506,0.087043,0.074804,0.068884,0.059197,0.047096]},{"section":11,"text":"The upper limbs are normal, so maybe it's starting in the lower extremities and moving up?","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.061726,0.11125,0.10719,0.098898,0.093341,0.093299,0.087426,0.085019,0.081085,0.069219,0.060517,0.051024],"unified_progress":[0.075821,0.094895,0.096922,0.099152,0.097341,0.09483,0.089017,0.087496,0.084609,0.071817,0.06008,0.04802]},{"section":12,"text":"But the upper limbs are okay here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046012,0.088976,0.094324,0.094207,0.094627,0.095617,0.094465,0.092871,0.088157,0.080899,0.072605,0.05724],"unified_progress":[0.068022,0.085382,0.089157,0.094067,0.096652,0.093317,0.092721,0.092377,0.086708,0.08407,0.067906,0.04962]},{"section":13,"text":"Wait, in Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome (GBS), the classic presentation is ascending paralysis, but sometimes it can start in the legs.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039774,0.077225,0.087167,0.095574,0.10055,0.10087,0.1005,0.095141,0.08648,0.084792,0.071122,0.060794],"unified_progress":[0.045956,0.069488,0.088993,0.094744,0.09826,0.10671,0.10056,0.097445,0.090552,0.085757,0.069252,0.052281]},{"section":14,"text":"The CSF findings are important here.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037966,0.080772,0.099354,0.10356,0.099849,0.093431,0.092654,0.087573,0.084175,0.083694,0.073188,0.063783],"unified_progress":[0.045171,0.073949,0.08704,0.097218,0.10059,0.098166,0.097388,0.093786,0.089932,0.088273,0.073437,0.05505]},{"section":15,"text":"High protein with normal glucose and mild lymphocytosis is typical for albuminocytologic dissociation in GBS, but wait, the cell count here is slightly elevated.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046571,0.092182,0.10516,0.10609,0.10177,0.095121,0.093956,0.086919,0.080192,0.073207,0.065918,0.05291],"unified_progress":[0.044514,0.083886,0.10015,0.10416,0.1088,0.10255,0.10461,0.089003,0.08205,0.072246,0.062137,0.045887]},{"section":16,"text":"Oh, maybe in the acute phase, the cell count can be a bit higher, but the protein is very high.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048712,0.092661,0.10571,0.10726,0.10313,0.0954,0.093336,0.08635,0.079099,0.072163,0.064432,0.051751],"unified_progress":[0.050673,0.083855,0.099058,0.10578,0.10892,0.10193,0.11112,0.08714,0.078484,0.069633,0.059386,0.044028]},{"section":17,"text":"Another thought: acute inflammatory demyelinating polyradiculoneuropathy (AIDP), which is a type of GBS.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037855,0.074489,0.087418,0.098401,0.10385,0.10319,0.10177,0.093619,0.084304,0.083779,0.068295,0.063031],"unified_progress":[0.042317,0.06535,0.084964,0.096577,0.10042,0.11062,0.1009,0.098387,0.090122,0.083663,0.069525,0.057166]},{"section":18,"text":"The absent reflexes are a key point because in GBS, reflexes are often lost early.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035002,0.074053,0.087161,0.094664,0.098705,0.098971,0.10063,0.095644,0.090245,0.085512,0.07602,0.063392],"unified_progress":[0.074574,0.072448,0.082755,0.090232,0.095409,0.096889,0.094843,0.093973,0.088571,0.083743,0.070783,0.055779]},{"section":19,"text":"The sensory testing is normal, which is more like AIDP rather than some other neuropathies where sensory is involved.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032101,0.070725,0.083811,0.091142,0.094907,0.096862,0.10003,0.098228,0.094791,0.090906,0.081148,0.065347],"unified_progress":[0.040322,0.069291,0.083378,0.091625,0.097715,0.098768,0.098958,0.098479,0.095318,0.093607,0.076754,0.055784]},{"section":20,"text":"The progression over a week is also consistent with GBS's typical course.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035987,0.072926,0.084128,0.0898,0.09268,0.093732,0.095576,0.09431,0.091172,0.091123,0.083218,0.075348],"unified_progress":[0.052738,0.06731,0.076431,0.084706,0.089651,0.092652,0.095502,0.095718,0.093588,0.095057,0.085307,0.071342]},{"section":21,"text":"The preceding infection (chest cold) fits with the post-infectious trigger, often from Campylobacter or a viral infection.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034446,0.070685,0.081713,0.089552,0.095814,0.1025,0.099509,0.097098,0.092262,0.090336,0.079283,0.066805],"unified_progress":[0.066459,0.095745,0.090563,0.087784,0.088641,0.092501,0.0893,0.091543,0.08542,0.081586,0.072246,0.058212]},{"section":22,"text":"Could it be something else?","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.32491,0.0529,0.053368,0.061978,0.064001,0.063775,0.062494,0.067994,0.067398,0.064433,0.06647,0.050276],"unified_progress":[0.22094,0.089479,0.067444,0.064806,0.07563,0.072863,0.089252,0.077715,0.073455,0.059574,0.055055,0.053792]},{"section":23,"text":"Maybe a spinal cord issue, like transverse myelitis?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029239,0.066113,0.061419,0.10137,0.10947,0.10167,0.10642,0.10199,0.095301,0.087984,0.079457,0.059572],"unified_progress":[0.039453,0.077256,0.072662,0.10199,0.11044,0.10328,0.10232,0.10045,0.092685,0.083434,0.069069,0.046961]},{"section":24,"text":"But the sensory is normal, and the distribution (lower limbs with normal upper limbs) might fit, but reflexes are absent.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026818,0.06229,0.074584,0.083741,0.091211,0.096375,0.10277,0.1039,0.1033,0.096769,0.090567,0.067669],"unified_progress":[0.043606,0.066829,0.079268,0.086797,0.097423,0.097567,0.098492,0.10233,0.099246,0.09731,0.078817,0.052314]},{"section":25,"text":"In myelitis, maybe spasticity and hyperreflexia?","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029053,0.064535,0.076714,0.086483,0.093848,0.098633,0.10363,0.10242,0.099448,0.093911,0.084559,0.066764],"unified_progress":[0.048282,0.065717,0.080232,0.088423,0.095766,0.10111,0.10002,0.10043,0.097081,0.092877,0.076592,0.053474]},{"section":26,"text":"Not sure.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.31547,0.051968,0.053073,0.061845,0.062818,0.064546,0.062187,0.070669,0.070554,0.065655,0.068348,0.052872],"unified_progress":[0.21574,0.082238,0.065493,0.06596,0.075131,0.074257,0.092682,0.081767,0.077749,0.0617,0.055187,0.052091]},{"section":27,"text":"Also, the CSF in myelitis might have more cells and protein, but the albuminocytologic dissociation is more GBS.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034792,0.072526,0.065709,0.10644,0.10755,0.099401,0.10276,0.09585,0.091663,0.084322,0.075952,0.06304],"unified_progress":[0.042981,0.074678,0.071761,0.099797,0.10719,0.099374,0.10583,0.09658,0.091198,0.084644,0.072543,0.053421]},{"section":28,"text":"Another possibility: motor neuron disease like ALS, but she's 24, which is young, and ALS is progressive but not this acute.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02686,0.060574,0.074305,0.084991,0.092588,0.09883,0.10374,0.10468,0.10086,0.098298,0.088733,0.065548],"unified_progress":[0.043249,0.071356,0.079345,0.085364,0.093538,0.095583,0.097704,0.10195,0.097853,0.10074,0.080579,0.052739]},{"section":29,"text":"Plus the preceding infection makes it less likely.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_p